                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d728">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.34119/994: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Howard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Asunción</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-27T12:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 27, 1937—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 1:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>29. Bis. Department’s 16, August 26, noon. I handed recognition note to the
                    Minister for Foreign Affairs at 10 a.m., today. Due to his indisposition the
                    interview was short and aside from expressing his pleasure he made no statements
                    of importance.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Buenos Aires.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Howard</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
